-- Guangdong Nuclear Now Has 30.8% of Kalahari Minerals
-- B y   J o h n   V i l j o e n
-- 2012-01-20T10:23:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-20/guangdong-nuclear-now-has-30-8-of-kalahari-minerals-correct-.html
(Corrects to clarify that Guangdong Nuclear has interest
in Kalahari Minerals’ stake in Extract.)  China Guangdong Nuclear Power Group
Co. has acceptances and pledges for 30.8 percent of  Kalahari
Minerals Plc (KAH) ’s issued share capital following its takeover
offer. This means that Guangdong Nuclear has a relevant interest
in Kalahari Minerals’ 42.74 percent holding in  Extract Resources
Ltd. (EXT) , a statement to the London Stock Exchange today shows.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Viljoen in London at 
